Author: sabat
Content:
Typical uncov BS. I don't know anything about the startup in question, but this:

earnings are so not Web 2.0. Profit is old economy bullshit, and Foldera knows it.

is complete crap. Earnings are a crucial part of what make Web 2.0 different than 1.0 -- this time, people are trying to figure out how to make money. Oh, and BTW, you actually can make a lot of money with a Web 2.0 business. Hell, ask the Plenty of Fish guy -- $5-10 million in annual revenue, one employee. Earnings are so not Web 2.0, my ass.
